code: library(imf.data)  # list all available time-series dt <- list_datasets() head(dt,3) #>               ID #> 297       AFRREO #> 41  AFRREO201410 #> 110 AFRREO201504 #>                                                            Description #> 297              Sub-Saharan Africa Regional Economic Outlook (AFRREO) #> 41  Sub-Saharan Africa Regional Economic Outlook (AFRREO) October 2014 #> 110   Sub-Saharan Africa Regional Economic Outlook (AFRREO) April 2015 # load IFS time-series IFS <- load_datasets("IFS")  # see possible values for dimension 'ref_area' tail(IFS$dimensions$ref_area) #>               Value                                      Description #> 273 1C_SRF_plus_EMU                               SRF (including EA) #> 274          1C_SRF                                    SRF Countries #> 275              F6                               Sub-Saharan Africa #> 276              7A WAEMU (West African Economic and Monetary Union) #> 277             A10                               Western Hemisphere #> 278             W00                  All Countries, excluding the IO  # get time-series for GDP of Portugal, with Annual frequency x <- IFS$get_series(freq = "A", ref_area = "PT", indicator = "NGDP_D_IX") head(x) #>   TIME_PERIOD   A.PT.NGDP_D_IX #> 1        1995  65.121159550493 #> 2        1996 66.6781968283958 #> 3        1997 69.2687835398304 #> 4        1998 71.9183372769496 #> 5        1999 74.3423648876999 #> 6        2000 76.8850736800294 # load DOT time-series DOT <- load_datasets("DOT")  y <- DOT$get_series(freq = "M",                     ref_area = "PT",                     indicator = "TMG_CIF_USD",                     counterpart_area = c("B0","W00"),                     start_period = "2022-01-01",                     end_period = "2022-12-31") head(y) #>   TIME_PERIOD M.PT.TMG_CIF_USD.B0 M.PT.TMG_CIF_USD.W00 #> 1     2022-01         5899.209507          8592.410482 #> 2     2022-02         6625.214152          9306.561169 #> 3     2022-03         7271.456185         10056.201211 #> 4     2022-04         6639.368158          9427.777556 #> 5     2022-05         7095.966482         10432.681421 #> 6     2022-06          6778.13623         10180.535376 HPDD <- load_datasets("HPDD")  HPDD$dimensions$indicator #>        Value       Description #> 1 GGXWDG_GDP Debt to GDP Ratio  x <- HPDD$get_series(freq = "A",                      ref_area = c("PT","ES"),                      indicator = "GGXWDG_GDP",                       start_period = "1974")  tail(x) #>    TIME_PERIOD  A.PT.GGXWDG_GDP  A.ES.GGXWDG_GDP #> 37        2010 96.1833185365076 60.0657865156585 #> 38        2011 111.389678797878 69.4619949496129 #> 39        2012 126.209890062282 85.4108429414156 #> 40        2013  129.00084417095 93.6746787462474 #> 41        2014 130.165394937574 99.2870917054055 #> 42        2015  128.97682231548 99.2599490376345

what: imf.data: An Interface to IMF (International Monetary Fund) Data JSON API — imf.data-package
title: imf.data: An Interface to IMF (International Monetary Fund) Data JSON API — imf.data-package
text: straightforward interface accessing IMF (International Monetary Fund) data JSON API, available https://data.imf.org/. package offers direct access primary API endpoints: Dataflow, DataStructure, CompactData. , provides intuitive interface exploring available dimensions attributes, well querying individual time-series datasets. Additionally, package implements rate limit API calls reduce chances exceeding service limits (limited 10 calls every 5 seconds) encountering response errors.
